name: Catholic Renewal Movement of Ethiopia
product_desc: Since about 2007 a quiet renewal has been happening within the Catholic Church of Ethiopia, bringing spiritual vitality to Catholics and non-Catholics alike. Because most of its 3000 members are very poor the movement has historically sought money from outsiders. However, the leaders of the movement have gradually identified dependency, rather than just poverty, as their problem. In February, 2014, they made the commitment to become self-sustaining and asked Hope In View, Inc, for technical help. The two organizations are embarking on a training program to help all of the movement’s members learn to start small businesses and to tithe their income to .help support their movement financially They are also training all 33 of their churches in better accounting methods. If they are successful in making this change, they will serve as role models for others trapped in dependency in this very poor country. They welcome other partners who could provide training and technical expertise.
high_concept: Sustainability for Ethiopian Catholic renewal movement

name: MoSera
product_desc:
Mo-Sera is a mobile based solution for recruitment and employment, in a country where  there's a gap between the jobs available and the avenues for getting the information about these jobs. Job ads mostly are published on newspapers, but reach only a small fraction of job seekers. 

Through Mo-Sera, jobseekers will be able to find jobs via SMS and IVR. Employers will then be able to instantly alert qualified candidates of available positions, directly to their phones. 

Through mobile services, companies and individuals can cover every tier of the work-force, which traditionally use word-to-mouth.

Mobile services are cheaper, and reach a wider more specialized target in Real Time speed.
high_concept: Jobs straight to your phone - Bridging the gap between what's available and who's looking
